:ParameterBindingc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition#ParameterBinding

Associates a constant term with a [fno:Parameter] in the specification of a [:PartiallyAppliedFunction]. The constant term is referenced via [:boundToTerm], the parameter via [:boundParameter].
Is defined by
https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition

CompositionMappingc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition#CompositionMapping

Connects one [fno:Function]'s [fno:Parameter] or [fno:Output] to another function's parameter or output. The properties used for this are [:mapFrom] and [:mapTo] . Exception: mapping from a parameter to an output allowed. Alternatively, a [:CompositionMapping] can link to a constant term via [:mapFromTerm] instead of [:mapFrom].
Is defined by
https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition
Term status
testing
is in domain of
mapFrom op, mapFromTerm op, mapTo op
is in range of
composedOf op

CompositionMappingEndpointc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition#CompositionMappingEndpoint

The `source` or `target` of a [:CompositionMapping], defining a combination of [fno:Function] and either [fno:Parameter] or [fno:Output].
Is defined by
https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition
Term status
testing
is in domain of
constituentFunction op, functionOutput op, functionParameter op
is in range of
mapFrom op, mapTo op

PartiallyAppliedFunctionc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition#PartiallyAppliedFunction

A [fno:Function] derived from another function by providing one or more, but not all parameter values.
Is defined by
https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition
Term status
testing
has super-classes
function c
is in domain of
::parameterBinding op, partiallyApplies op

appliesop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition#applies

Indicates that the [fno:Function] in the subject is a distinct application of the function in the object of the triple. The distinct application has the same properties as the original. This construction allows for making assertions about different applications of the same function.
Is defined by
https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition
Term status
testing
has domain
function c
has range
function c

partiallyAppliesop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition#partiallyApplies

Expresses that the [fno:Function] in the subject is a partial application of the [fno:Function] referenced by the object. It is expected that the partial application provides a constant value for at least one of the function's [fno:Parameter]s. If no parameter values are specified the use of [:partiallyApplies] is equivalent to [:applies].
Is defined by
https://w3id.org/function/vocabulary/composition
Term status
testing
has domain
PartiallyAppliedFunction c
has range
function c
